                <p xml:id="CH1a0907-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0907_CHANT_016-35a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-01T23:29:00.345+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0907_CHANT_016-35a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-01T23:38:56.028+09:00">一言而急，                                                                駟馬不及。                                                                故惡言不出口，                    苟語不留耳，此謂君子也。</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0907_CHANT_016-36a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-01T23:42:44.074+09:00">明李贄《與馬伯時書》：“我此一等與世上人眞不同，沒有一點欺心罪過。”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0907_CHANT_016-43a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-10-14T03:54:37.067+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0907_CHANT_016-43a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-10-14T03:54:46.101+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0907_CHANT_006-10a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#guest" modified="2022-01-19T01:29:56.121+09:00">"I have learned that eating the meat of an excellent horse without drinking ale</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0907_CHANT_006-10a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#guest" modified="2022-01-19T01:30:11.27+09:00">kills."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0907_CHANT_006-10a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#guest" modified="2022-01-19T01:37:35.281+09:00">and besieged him.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0907_CHANT_016-54a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#guest" modified="2022-03-31T03:54:30.924+09:00">and the first effective signs of ruin</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0907_CHANT_016-54a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#guest" modified="2022-03-31T03:56:51.184+09:00">issue forth from this (source).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0907_CHANT_016-54a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#guest" modified="2022-03-31T04:02:12.907+09:00">The Yangzi's and the Yellow River's great floods originate from the ant nests</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0907_CHANT_016-57a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-04-21T05:29:39.889+09:00">(Note that potentially one might take this in egg-headed Oxford sense to mean: Having seen disappearance one understands the (former) existence. But this does not fit the context of this book.) (CH) / Compare the example in SY 6.10. </seg>
                </p>
